Extract all words from tamil wikipedia dump.

Get the wikipedia dump from the following url
http://dumps.wikimedia.org/tawiki/latest/

tawiki-latest-pages-articles.xml.tar.bz2

extract it using the following command.

Tar xvjf  tawiki-latest-pages-articles.xml.tar.bz2




1. shell script  seperate the words

cat line.sh 
#!/bin/bash 
for WORD in `cat tawiki-latest-pages-articles.xml` 
do 
    echo $WORD 
done 



Run the script
sh ./line.sh > all 



2. sort it


sort all > all.sorted 


3. find unique words

uniq all.sorted > all.unique 


4. 

To remove all english charecters

tr  [:graph:]  ' ' < all.unique> all.tr


5.
To remove all symbols

tr  "\012\015\041\042\043\044\045\046\047\050\051\053\054\055\056\057\060\061\062\06‌​3\064\065\066\067\070\071\073\074\075\076\077\100\101\102\103\104\105\106\107\110\‌​111\112\113\114\115\116\117\120\121\122\123\124\125\126\127\130\131\132\133\135\1‌​40\173\174\175" '\n' < all.tr > all.tr1 




6.

To remove leading spaces and blank lines
 cat all.tr1 | sed -e 's/^[ \t]*//' | grep -v ^$ > all.trim


7.

Sort and unique the file
sort all.trim | uniq > all.sort.unique


8.

cp all.sort.unique tamil.sort.unique



9. 

python to extract only tamil words.


find_tamil.py

it will create a file with only tamil words

python fine_tamil.py

output : tamil-words.txt


10.  sed '/^$/d' tamil-words.txt > final-tamil.txt


11. count the number of words available

wc -l final-tamil.txt
1309490 tamil-words.txt

